      <scopecontent id="aspace_800ce5b0dec26f21ca9ed197407408f0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This finding aid encompasses accessions of single manuscripts and small groups of manuscripts and other papers, by or pertaining to the English writer Mary Russell Mitford (1787-1855), which the library has acquired from various sources.</p>
         <p>The collection includes professional correspondence regarding Mitford's book <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Our Village: Sketches of Rural Character and Scenery</part>
            </title> and other writings, personal correspondence, and manuscripts of poems and dramatic works. Correspondents include W. C. Bennett, Benjamin Robert Haydon, William Morgan Kinsey, Thomas Noon Talfourd, Abraham John Valpy, and Julia Rattray Waddington.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
